f=Cybersecurity/keyring/marketplace/access-control-policy/SKILL.md · in=Identity access management grounded zero-trust principles: RBAC, least privilege, MFA enforcement, quarterly access reviews aligned ISO 27001 (A.5.15, A.8.2, A.8.3). policy defines who access what, they authenticate, often access reviewed, exceptions handled. · p=Access control fundamental security control you don't know who access what, you don't verify access still needed, you operating trust rather verification. structured access control policy clearly defined tiers, authentication requirements, review cadences turns access source risk managed process. · wu=Designing reviewing access control model system, application, data store., Determining authentication requirements (MFA method, session timeout) given asset classification., Setting auditing role-based access control (RBAC) structures., Planning conducting quarterly access reviews., Investigating potential privilege creep dormant accounts. · h2:Access Control Matrix=\| Asset Category \| Classification \| Access Method \| MFA Requirement \| Session Timeout \| Review Frequency \| · h2:Access Control Matrix=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Access Control Matrix=\| RESTRICTED Data \| Extreme \| Hardware MFA + Zero Trust \| FIDO2 + Backup \| 1 hour \| Monthly \| · h2:Access Control Matrix=\| Cloud Infrastructure \| Very High \| Identity Center SSO \| Hardware + TOTP \| 4 hours \| Monthly \| · h2:Access Control Matrix=\| Development Platform \| High \| Platform MFA + SSH Keys \| TOTP + SSH Cert \| 8 hours \| Quarterly \| · h2:Access Control Matrix=\| Financial Systems \| Very High \| Provider MFA \| Hardware Token \| 1 hour \| Monthly \| · h2:Access Control Matrix=\| Business Intelligence \| Moderate \| SSO Integration \| TOTP \| 24 hours \| Semi-Annual \| · h2:Access Control Matrix=\| Marketing Platforms \| Public/Internal \| Platform Native \| Platform MFA \| 7 days \| Annual \| · h3:Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)=Access granted based job function, identity. role defined set permissions, users assigned roles rather directly permissions. ensures consistency, auditability, ease review. · h3:Least Privilege=identity human machine gets minimum access required perform function. more. default answer "no"; access justified documented granted. · h3:Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)=interactive human access requires MFA. method scales sensitivity asset: · h3:Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)=**FIDO2 hardware keys** restricted critical systems, **TOTP hardware key** cloud infrastructure, **TOTP platform MFA** development platforms, **Platform MFA** standard business systems · h3:Regular Access Reviews=Access reviewed schedule matches sensitivity asset: · h3:Regular Access Reviews=**Monthly**: Restricted data, cloud infrastructure, financial systems, **Quarterly**: Development platforms, **Semi-Annual**: Business intelligence, **Annual**: Marketing public-facing platforms · h3:Regular Access Reviews=Reviews verify grant still needed, identify revoke unused excessive access, detect dormant orphaned accounts. · h2:Zero-Trust Architecture=access control model assumes zero implicit trust. access request authenticated, authorized, encrypted regardless whether originates inside outside network perimeter. Key architectural components: **Identity Provider (IdP)** single source identity truth MFA enforcement **Cloud Infrastructure** AWS Identity Center, IAM Roles, Federated Accounts permission boundaries **Development** GitHub Organization SSO, CI/CD scoped service accounts **Business Systems** Financial, Marketing, Security tools tiered MFA requirements · h3:Quarterly Access Review Process=**Inventory**: List human machine identities scope. **Compare**: Current access against role-based entitlements. **Identify**: Over-provisioned accounts, dormant accounts, role mismatches. **Review**: finding reviewed data/asset owner. **Remediate**: Unjustified access revoked (revoke-then-appeal). **Document**: Results logged; systemic issues escalated. · h3:Dormant Account Detection=Accounts authentication activity 90+ days flagged dormant. Dormant accounts automatically disabled after notification account owner manager. Disabled accounts deleted after additional days unless explicitly reactivated. · h3:Break-Glass Procedure=Emergency high-privilege access is: · h3:Break-Glass Procedure=Pre-defined pre-authorized named scenarios, Time-limited (auto-revokes after approved window), Monitored real-time (alert use), Reviewed after use confirm necessity, Logged full detail audit · of=`## Access Control Review: [scope/system] \· Asset classification: [tier per matrix] \· MFA requirement: [method] \· Session timeout: [duration] \· Review cadence: [frequency] \· Last review: [date] \· Findings: [over-provisioned accounts \· dormant accounts \· role mismatches]` · pr=**Least privilege default** access justified, assumed. **MFA mandatory interactive human access** method scales asset sensitivity. **Access without review risk** review cadences exist tier; missed reviews findings. **Zero trust means zero implicit trust** request authenticated authorized. **Dormant accounts risks** hasn't used days, it's disabled. **Break-glass defined, ad-hoc** emergency access pre-planned, monitored, reviewed. · f=IdP place document access manual matrix; label controls "manual provisional until IdP implemented.", Unable enforce MFA system flag exception compensating controls time-boxed remediation plan., Organization small quarterly reviews extend bi-annual understanding risk accepted. · b:with Other Skills=**classification-policy** (Hack23/cia companion): defines PUBLIC INTERNAL CONFIDENTIAL RESTRICTED tiers skill references., **information-security-policy** (Hack23/cia companion): overarching ISMS policy skill implements., **iso-27001-controls** (Hack23/cia companion): maps specific controls audit evidence., **keyring's identity-lifecycle** (Cybersecurity): operational JML workflow operates within policy framework., **keyring's access-reviews** (Cybersecurity): periodic recertification implements skill's review cadence., **relay** (AI Agents): applies least-privilege doctrine agent/machine identity., **warden** (Cybersecurity): access control gaps review findings risks warden's register.